  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/b15b5df14ba749b8a5e1dcf3a111a591",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Club Name is primarily a club about Dungeons and Dragons.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">But our masters run different systems, and we will tell you why you should leave your comfort zone and play not only classic fantasy, but also World of Darkness and Kult.</span></p>",
      "title": "Why should you play different systems?"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/49396c4de89648f9a74b09b9b455a7a0",
      "title": "World of Darkness",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The World of Darkness game system allows you to play as a supernatural creature in a modern environment.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Typically, this is a vampire in the Vampire: The Maquerade line.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">This system, unlike Dungeons and Dragons, is focused on creating a game that tackles ambiguous themes.</span><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\"> </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The World of Darkness is a gloomy inversion of our world, the night streets of modern megalopolises, in which no one can be trusted, not even their coterie mates.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Here, not every dispute can be resolved with fists, the character, although a vampire, is not immortal, and the best fight is the one that did not take place.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">There are no mindless monsters here, and even the most hideous creatures of dark magic have a mind behind them.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The World of Darkness opens up a huge space for social interaction - almost any enemy can be tricked, charmed or made into an ally. If you indulge your inner Beast, you will quickly turn into a crazy uncontrollable monster. The character constantly balances between his own humanity and the impulses of the inner predator, often making difficult moral decisions.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Gothic, gloom, brutality, intrigue and betrayal - all this, together with one of the most flexible systems for creating a character, creates a sense of vampire noir, which is so memorable for the game Vampires: Bloodlines.</span></span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/d6dfe7eeba874ee0842184f341e8e97e",
      "title": "Kult | Divinity Lost",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Kult is a system in which you act as a person who has experienced a traumatic event for the psyche, after which he began to see things that others do not.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Monsters and strange places are everywhere, and the rest of the people don't notice.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Am I crazy, or has the world always been this way?</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Kult gives an experience not only of horror, but also of the complete unreliability of the world. In this system, the player is not a mighty hero in armor and with a fiery sword, and not even a deadly vampire. He is just a man in a dangerous and crazy world filled with monsters and horrors. And this world is very unstable. There may be a portal to hell in the basement, and the neighbor boy will turn into an ancient god.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The main idea of the Kult is the awakening of the inner divinity, the hidden potential of each person, which is hunted by all creatures in this nightmarish world. Even experience at the end of the session is gained by players learning something new about the Reality hidden behind the Illusion. The result is a mix of The Matrix and Silent Hill with massive occult references.<span class=\"jCAhz\"> </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">If you want to try something darker and more serious than Dungeons and Dragons, then these systems are perfect for you. Do not forget, of course, about game ethics - if you have topics that you would not like to discuss in a tabletop role-playing game, let the master know about them.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/581a0983f4674f54aeb5be0014abd61e",
      "title": "Try something new!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Each game system is a special experience, like a new movie genre or an exotic dessert.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">So, if you see unfamiliar words in the schedule, think about opening a new experience.</span></p>"
    }
  ],
